FBIS4-18260 "drweu063_p_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-063 Daily Report 31 Mar 1994 GREECE Spokesman Expresses Concern Over Patriarchy's Safety Spokesman Expresses Concern Over Patriarchy's Safety NC3103123194 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in Greek 1130 GMT 31 Mar 94 NC3103123194 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network Greek BFN [Text] Government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos expressed his concern over the upsurge in violence in Turkey following yesterday's bomb attack against the Ecumenical Patriarchy in Istanbul. Venizelos stressed a point in U.S. President Bill Clinton's letter to Greek Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou and Turkish Prime Minister Tansu Ciller in which Clinton raises the issue of the status and protection of the Ecumenical Patriarchy.
